description: Note 1. July-2019: This image is still categorized as "Lacking data", one of 20 pics, which I don't understand? What is missing? M27, a LRGBHaOIII picture. The raw data was taken 27. Aug & 2. Sep-2016. Edit info. added 6 Febr-2017. The exposure time is mentioned here. 1. In S&T, http://www.skyandtelescope.com/online-gallery/m27-lhaoiii-rgb-picture-1sec-5min-exposures/ 2. in a Danish astro-forum, http://www.forum.2astro.dk/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=8310 The translated info./copy & paste info.: M27 was this time composed as a L-Ha-OIII-R,G,B picture. In total ~5.9hours exposure where the Ha part consist of 12*5min subs and the OIII part consist of 14*5min subs. My home build observatory is placed in my front yard/in the "red light" polution zone, have a look here, Red Zone Kind regards Niels
title: M27, a LRGBHaOIII picture
